President Muhammadu Buhari will not make any broadcast on COVID -19 updates today.
Special Adviser on Media and Publicity Femi Adesina made this known on Monday afternoon on Twitter.
“No presidential broadcast on COVID-19 updates today.
“None was planned. Rather, the Presidential Task Force will during its usual media briefings bring the nation up to speed on the next steps,” he tweeted.
SGF Boss Mustapha, head of the Presidential Task Force on COVID-19 , would update the nation during its briefings.